To make [[../libfprint|libfprint]] useful, we need to integrate it into existing software. Projects to do that are tracked below.

== pam_fprint ==

[[../pam_fprint|pam_fprint]] is a [[http://www.kernel.org/pub/linux/libs/pam/whatispam.html|PAM module]] ''(Pluggable Authentication Module)'' that uses libfprint for authentication. In other words, it allows you to login to your Linux system in the normal way, except you scan your finger instead of typing a password.

